This paper deals with the problem of subjective visual interpretation in computer vision, which is a core topic in the field of computer vision. The paper proposes a novel model for capturing subjectivity in image processing and introduces a new dataset for this purpose. The paper also compares several deep learning methods for this task. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) aspects, as it proposes a model for predicting subjective noun attributes in images. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

The paper uses deep learning methods for the task of predicting subjective noun attributes in images, which is a common approach in machine learning. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper proposes a novel model for capturing subjectivity in image processing, which involves the use of context information and tensor multiplication. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is a core topic in multimedia computing. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
